Contemporary Art in Africa
Frederick A. Praeger | 1968 | ISBN: 0269992839 | English | 196 pages | PDF | 23.4 MB

There has been a profusion of books on traditional African art in recent years. Though many of these are excellent they tend to create the impression that artistic expression is a thing of the past in Africa and that nothing of value is being produced today. The simple reason for this is that modern art is a fairly new phenomenon in Africa
